be anticipated, even understood, offering hope for dealing with and neutralizing it. Hans Kribbe draws on a range of political ideas to provide insight into the strongman's seemingly irrational and idiosyncratic behaviour and to better understand how he wields power and to what end. With the world's largest economies, including Europe's key ally, as well as strategic neighbouring states controlled by strongmen - Xi Jinping, Donald Trump, Vladimir Putin, and Recep Tayyip Erdogan - Europe must learn to adapt and respond if it is to beat them at their own game.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBalance of power. 0aHeads of state. 0aPower (Social sciences). 0aRhetoricxPolitical aspects. 70(DE-588)4036824-50(DE-627)1046372690(DE-576)209020679aMacht2gnd 70(DE-588)4046588-30(DE-627)10619755X0(DE-576)209070153aPolitisches Verhalten2gnd 70(DE-588)4072885-70(DE-627)1060939320(DE-576)209188553aInternationale Politik2gnd 70(DE-588)4130306-40(DE-627)1057035400(DE-576)20961787XaRegierungschef2gnd 70(DE-588)4168427-80(DE-627)1054176530(DE-576)209915501aMachtpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4359546-70(DE-627)1813040070(DE-576)211615161aHerrschaftssystem2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022800471440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228004714423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228004714/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles